    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
      <article class="lg:col-span-2">
        <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-red-brand mb-2">Compliance · April 2026 · 10 min read</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4 leading-tight">Fire Extinguisher Inspection in Sacramento, CA: What Every Business Owner Needs to Know</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">If you own or manage a commercial property in Sacramento, CA, your fire extinguishers are a legal requirement with specific inspection schedules enforced by the Sacramento Fire Department. Here's exactly what NFPA 10 and the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR) require, what inspections cost, and how to avoid violations.</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3">Sacramento Fire Extinguisher Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The City of Sacramento enforces the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR), requiring all commercial properties to maintain portable fire extinguishers in compliance with <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10</a>. Sacramento's commercial landscape spans the Downtown K Street and Golden 1 Center arena district, the Midtown arts and dining corridor, the Railyards mixed-use development, and significant state government office buildings throughout the Capitol complex. As California's capital city, Sacramento has a high concentration of institutional and government building fire protection compliance alongside standard commercial obligations.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Monthly Visual Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Monthly visual inspections can be performed by trained building staff. Verify each unit is in place, unobstructed, pressure gauge reads in the operating range, tamper seal is intact, and pull pin is present. Document every check — absence of monthly records significantly increases liability exposure.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Annual Professional Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Annual inspections must be performed by a licensed technician. California requires fire extinguisher service contractors to hold an OSFM license from the California State Fire Marshal's Office. Verify licensing at osfm.fire.ca.gov before scheduling service. The technician inspects all components and attaches a dated service tag. Failed units must be immediately serviced, recharged, or replaced.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">6-Year Internal Examination & 12-Year Hydrostatic Testing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every six years, stored-pressure units must be internally examined for corrosion and agent degradation. At 12 years, cylinders must pass hydrostatic pressure testing — units that fail are condemned. Your service provider should track these intervals based on each unit's manufacture date.</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Inspection Costs in Sacramento, CA</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6"><table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse"><thead><tr class="bg-gray-50"><th class="text-left p-3 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Service</th><th class="text-left p-3 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Cost Range</th><th class="text-left p-3 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Frequency</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">Annual Inspection & Tag</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$16–$40 per unit</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Every 12 months</td></tr><tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">Recharge (ABC Dry Chemical)</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$20–$50</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">As needed</td></tr><tr><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">6-Year Internal Examination</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$26–$55 per unit</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Every 6 years</td></tr><tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">12-Year Hydrostatic Test</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$32–$70 per unit</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Every 12 years</td></tr><tr><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">New 10 lb ABC Extinguisher</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$45–$95</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Replacement</td></tr><tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">Class K Kitchen Extinguisher</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$85–$175</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Commercial kitchens</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Common Violations in Sacramento</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 mb-8"><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Expired tags in Midtown restaurant and entertainment spaces — high tenant turnover in Sacramento's growing dining scene</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Missing Class K extinguishers in Downtown and Midtown commercial kitchens</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Inadequate coverage in state government office buildings where compliance oversight is shared between DGS and Sacramento FD</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Missing Class B coverage in Railyards industrial and warehouse operations</span></div></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Sacramento Fire Prevention Contacts</h2>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-5 mb-6"><p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Sacramento Fire Department</strong></p><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">1231 I Street, Suite 401, Sacramento, CA 95814</p><p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Phone: (916) 808-1300</p><p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>California State Fire Marshal's Office</strong></p><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Phone: (916) 445-8200</p></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often do fire extinguishers need to be inspected in Sacramento, CA?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Monthly visual inspections by building staff, annual professional inspections by a licensed technician, 6-year internal examinations, and 12-year hydrostatic testing per NFPA 10 and the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR).</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does a fire extinguisher inspection cost in Sacramento, CA?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Annual inspections in the Sacramento metro typically cost $16–$40 per unit. 6-year internal examinations run $26–$55. 12-year hydrostatic tests cost $32–$70. Volume discounts apply for 20+ units.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who can inspect fire extinguishers in Sacramento, CA?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Monthly visual checks by trained staff. Annual, 6-year, and 12-year service by a licensed technician. California requires fire extinguisher service contractors to hold an OSFM license from the California State Fire Marshal's Office. Verify licensing at osfm.fire.ca.gov before scheduling service.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What are the most common fire extinguisher violations in Sacramento?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The most common violations cited by the Sacramento Fire Department include: Expired tags in Midtown restaurant and entertainment spaces — high tenant turnover in Sacramento's growing dining scene; Missing Class K extinguishers in Downtown and Midtown commercial kitchens.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does Sacramento require fire extinguishers in all commercial buildings?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. The California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR) requires portable fire extinguishers in all commercial, industrial, and multi-family residential buildings. Type, size, and placement depend on occupancy classification and hazard level per NFPA 10.</p></div></div>
